f:\mathbb R\to\mathbb R 
\exists a,b\in \mathbb R^+~~~~\text{such that}~~~~|f(x)|\le a|x|+b.
\delta > 0
|x - y| < \delta
|y| < k \delta
y
|f(x) - f(y)| < 1
|f(0) - f(y)| < k
|f(y)| \le |f(0) - f(y)| + |f(0)| < k + |f(0)|
\delta > 0
z \ne 0
m(z) \le |z|/\delta + 1
m(z) = \min\{k \in \mathbb N \colon |z| < k \delta\}
|f(z)| < m(z) + |f(0)| \le |z|/\delta + 1 + |f(0)|
